Key Match Events: Mohammad Rizwan and Saud Shakeel hit identical half-centuries
Pakistan dismissed Netherlands for 205 in 41 overs
Haris Rauf took 3 wickets for 43 runs
Bas de Leede took 4 wickets for 62 runs for Netherlands
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan won the toss and decided to field
Netherlands won their first World Cup match since 2011 after coming through the qualifying event
Post-Match Reflections: The Dutch looked on course for a win but Pakistan kept chipping away
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Rajiv Gandhi International Cricket Stadium in Hyderabad
Pakistan's middle-order batsmen Rizwan and Shakeel steadied the ship with a fourth-wicket partnership of 120
